to the editor a june 7 letter writer bemoans the cycle in which the new elite displaces artists and writers from the culturally vital urban neighborhoods created by them i would describe this cycle more fully and be less cheerful about it than even the writer artists and writers do not create such neighborhoods in a vacuum too often landlords allow artists and writers who can pay higher rents than legal industrial users to illegally convert manufacturing space into residential quarters this has happened in williamsburg and red hook which groups lose out before the bohemians industrial users and the immigrant and working classes who depend on those jobs bill shockney exec dir southwest brooklyn industrial development corporation brooklyn june 8 2002

